  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Attic comedian from the 4th cent. BC. The titles
    of four plays have survived (Δευκαλίων/Deukalíōn, Ἰάλεμος/Iálemos or ‘Simple Simon
    Κάλλαισχρος/Kállaischros - it is unclear from this name whether the play is about a historical
    or fictitious person Κένταυρος/Kéntauros). There are six fragments extant which are ineffectual except
    for fragment 3 (parody of Plato)...." Nesselrath, Heinz-Günther (Göttingen). "Ophelion." Brill's New Pauly.
